FilterData API

API for normalization and quality scoring of contact data before loading it into CRM systems, marketing platforms and lead databases.

FilterData standardizes phone numbers, emails and personal names and returns a technical quality score that helps detect problematic records before they enter business systems.

What the API does

FilterData accepts contact data and returns:

• normalized values
• data quality score (QC)
• QC breakdown for each field
• warnings about suspicious records

Supported fields:

phone

name

email

Example request

POST

https://filterdata.ru/docs#/Normalize/demo_normalize_api_v1_demo_normalize_post

Body

{
  "phone": "8 (999) 123-45-67",
  "name": "иван иванов",
  "email": "EXAMPLE@mail.com"
}
Example response
{
  "phone": "+79991234567",
  "name": "Иван Иванов",
  "email": "example@mail.com",
  "qc": 0,
  "qc_breakdown": {
    "phone": 0,
    "name": 0,
    "email": 0
  },
  "warnings": []
}
Batch API (processing up to 1000 contacts)

For migration of large databases or bulk imports the API supports batch processing.

Endpoint:

POST /api/v1/batch

Maximum:

1000 contacts per request

Example request

{
  "contacts": [
    {
      "phone": "8 (999) 123-45-67",
      "name": "иван иванов",
      "email": "EXAMPLE@mail.com"
    },
    {
      "phone": "+7 (912) 000-00-00",
      "name": "Ivanov Иван",
      "email": " USER@MAIL.RU "
    }
  ]
}

Example response

{
  "results": [
    {
      "phone": "+79991234567",
      "name": "Иван Иванов",
      "email": "example@mail.com",
      "qc": 0,
      "qc_breakdown": {
        "phone": 0,
        "name": 0,
        "email": 0
      },
      "warnings": []
    },
    {
      "phone": "+79120000000",
      "name": "Ivanov Иван",
      "email": "user@mail.ru",
      "qc": 2,
      "qc_breakdown": {
        "phone": 0,
        "name": 2,
        "email": 0
      },
      "warnings": ["name_mixed_alphabet_risk"]
    }
  ]
}
Data Quality Levels (QC)

QC indicates technical quality of the record.

QC	Level	Description
0	VALID	Data is correct
1	ACCEPTABLE	Acceptable but not perfect
2	RISK	Suspicious data
3	PARTIAL	Incomplete or invalid
4	MISSING	Field missing

Example of risky data

Иванov Ivan

Mixed Cyrillic and Latin characters.

